'''聖座－美國關係'''是[[美国|美国]]和[[罗马教廷|罗马教廷]]之间的双边关系。首席美国外交官员是卡丽斯塔·金里奇大使，她于2017年12月22日正式上任。罗马教廷的代表是于2016年4月12日就职的[[圣座大使|圣座大使]]克里斯托弗·皮埃尔大主教。美国驻罗马教廷大使馆位于罗马的多米齐亚纳别墅。驻美国大使馆位于[[华盛顿特区|华盛顿特区]]，位于西北马萨诸塞大道3339号。
== 历史 ==
=== 1797年至1867年 ===
从1797年的[[乔治·华盛顿|乔治·华盛顿]]总统和教宗[[庇護六世|庇护六世]]任内，到1867年[[安德鲁·约翰逊|安德鲁·约翰逊]]总统和教宗[[庇护九世|庇护九世]]任内，美国与[[教皇国|教皇国]]保持着领事关系。从1848年[[詹姆斯·诺克斯·波尔克|詹姆斯·诺克斯·波尔克]]总统任内到1867年[[安德鲁·约翰逊|安德鲁·约翰逊]]总统任内，教皇以教皇国元首的身份与美国建立了外交关系，但没有建立大使级外交关系。1867年2月28日，美国国会通过立法，禁止美国今后向罗马教廷的外交使团提供任何资金。这一决定是基于美国日益高涨的反天主教情绪，<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.iwp.edu/news_publications/detail/us-vatican-relations-25th-anniversary-and-a-new-president|title= US-Vatican Relations: 25th Anniversary and a New President|first1= Thomas P.|last1= Melady|first2= Timothy R.|last2= Stebbins|date= Spring 2009|publisher=  [[The_Institute_of_World_Politics|The Institute of World Politics]]|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140116134230/http://www.iwp.edu/news_publications/detail/us-vatican-relations-25th-anniversary-and-a-new-president|archive-date= 2014-01-16|dead-url= no|access-date= 2011-05-01}}</ref>以及天主教徒玛丽·苏拉特因参与阴谋暗杀[[亚伯拉罕·林肯|亚伯拉罕·林肯]]总统而被定罪并处以绞刑。她的儿子约翰·苏拉特也是天主教徒，被指控与[[约翰·威尔克斯·布斯|约翰·威尔克斯·布斯]]密谋暗杀亚伯拉罕·林肯。他得到了罗马天主教会的庇护，逃到意大利，在那里担任教皇义勇兵。还有一项指控称，教皇禁止了新教宗教仪式的庆祝活动。此前，新教宗教仪式每周都在美国驻罗马部长的家中举行，地点在梵蒂冈城墙之内。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lpca.us/us%20and%20vatican.htm|title= The United States and the Holy See: The Long Road|first= Jim|last= Nicholson|author-link= Jim Nicholson (Secretary of Veterans Affairs)|year= 2004|publisher= Legionnaires Praying for the Clergy Apostolate|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070527084930/http://www.lpca.us/us%20and%20vatican.htm|archive-date= 2007-05-27|dead-url= no|quote= The critics finally won out in 1867 when Congress withdrew all funding for the legation in Rome. The apparent reason was a rumor relating to the religious freedom of Protestants in the Papal States. From the beginning of the legation in Rome, Papal authorities had allowed the celebration of Protestant religious services in the home of the American Minister. When the services grew, they were moved to a rented apartment under the seal of the American Legation to accommodate the participants. The news floating around Washington and being reported in the ''New York Times'' was that the Pope had forced the protestant group outside the walls of Rome. This, according to Rufus King, the American Minister himself, was untrue in its entirety.}}</ref>
=== 1867年至1984年 ===
从1867年到1984年，美国与罗马教廷没有外交关系。几位总统指定了私人特使定期访问罗马教廷，讨论国际人道主义和政治问题。邮政总局局长[[吉姆·法利|吉姆·法利]]是第一位代表。法利是第一个与罗马教廷关系正常化的高级政府官员。1933年，英国邮政署长与苏联外交委员利特维诺夫乘坐意大利的“萨沃亚孔特号”班轮启程前往欧洲。在意大利，法利拜会了教皇[[庇护十一世|庇护十一世]]，并与1939年继任教皇的红衣主教[[庇护十二世|派契利]]共进晚餐。<ref>{{cite book|last= Farley|first= James|author-link= James Farley|title= Jim Farley's Story: The Roosevelt Years|publisher = [[McGraw_Hill_Financial|McGraw Hill]]|year= 1948|location= New York City|url= https://archive.org/stream/jimfarleysstory017770mbp/jimfarleysstory017770mbp_djvu.txt|isbn= 978-1430450610}}</ref>从1939年到1950年，迈伦·查尔斯·泰勒为[[富兰克林·D·罗斯福|富兰克林·D·罗斯福]]和[[哈里·S·杜鲁门|哈里·S·杜鲁门]]总统担任这一职务。<ref>John S. Conway, "Myron C. Taylor's Mission to the Vatican 1940–1950." ''Church History'' 44.1 (1975): 85-99.</ref>

[[尼克松|尼克松]]、[[杰拉尔德·福特|福特]]、[[吉米·卡特|卡特]]和[[里根|里根]]总统也任命了与教皇的私人使节。除了杜鲁门<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1956/05/21/archives/the-trumans-meet-the-pope-during-vatican-visit-trumans-visit-pope.html |title=The Trumans Meet the Pope During Vatican Visit; Truman in Cutaway Coat |newspaper=New York Times |accessdate=2021-03-04 |archive-date=2018-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617194234/https://www.nytimes.com/1956/05/21/archives/the-trumans-meet-the-pope-during-vatican-visit-trumans-visit-pope.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[艾森豪威尔|艾森豪威尔]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/travels/president/eisenhower-dwight-d |title=Travels of President Dwight D. Eisenhower |publisher=U.S. Department of State Office of the Historian |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/63goC10Wd?url=http://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/travels/president/eisenhower-dwight-d |archive-date=2011-12-04 |dead-url= yes }}</ref>、[[约翰·肯尼迪|肯尼迪]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/travels/president/kennedy-john-f |title=Travels of President John F. Kennedy |publisher=U.S. Department of State Office of the Historian |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/63goGt8ev?url=http://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/travels/president/kennedy-john-f |archive-date=2011-12-04 |dead-url= yes }}</ref>、[[林登·约翰逊|约翰逊]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/paul_vi/travels/sub-index/index_onu.htm |title=Pope Paul VI Visit to the United Nations, 1964 |publisher=Vatican.va |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6FBmvicRJ?url=http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/paul_vi/travels/sub-index/index_onu.htm |archive-date=2013-03-17 |dead-url= no }}</ref>以及后来所有的总统，还有那些穿着黑色衣服和面纱的第一夫人们，都在寻求教皇的祝福，通常是在他们执政的头几个月里，而且通常都是去梵蒂冈进行的。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/travels/president/nixon-richard-m |title=Travels of President Richard M. Nixon |publisher=U.S. Department of State Office of the Historian |archive-url=h